<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=99074280452225></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f99074280452225><tr><td id=headerrow><span id=sj><a href=/strategy/classes.html?class=3&mid=99074280452225>RE: Maxing out weapon skills</a></span></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?id=35651><span id=Guru>Keyeluke</span></a>, <span id=Guru>Guru</span><br><span id=notbold>192 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Thu, May 24th 6:20 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[2.80]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Oh yes, there are caps on all skills.  To the best of my knowledge, these are the caps for monks:<br><br>1HB, 2HB, Offense, Defense, Dual Wield  252<br>Double Attack 250<br>H2H  245<br>Dodge 230<br>Block, Riposte 225<br>All special attacks 225<br>Disarm, FD, ID, Mend 200<br><br>Most of the other skills cap at 200.  Bind wound caps at 210, sneak at 113.<br><br>Combat skills are level capped at Lvl*5 + 5 with exceptions - Defense lvl*5, Dual Wield lvl*7 or lvl*7+7 (could never figure that one out), Offense gets an extra 5 at lvl 35 (I think) and another 5 some time in the 40s.<br><br>Hope that answers your question.<br><br>Now two counter-questions for my esteemed brothers on this site:<br><br>My defense is lagging - it is not maxing out in each level.  Anyone else experience this?<br><br>What is the point of Mend capping at 200 when it always works after 100?  I've read, and believe, that mend's chance of success is a straight percentage, and I have never seen it fail since I got it to 100.  The amount of damage healed is always 25%.<br><br>Keyeluke<br>Monk of the Silent Fist, 40th Circle<br>Strange Brew<br>Druzzil Ro<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
	   <span style='font-weight: normal; font-size: 9px;'>[<a href=#top>Top</a>]</span></tr>
	   </form></table><ul>
<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=99077309665912></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f99077309665912><tr><td id=headerrow><span id=sj><a href=/strategy/classes.html?class=3&mid=99077309665912>RE: Maxing out weapon skills</a></span></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?id=39551><span id=Guru>Osano</span></a>, <span id=Guru>Guru</span><br><span id=notbold>171 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Fri, May 25th 2:44 AM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[4.76]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Clarification:  Skills have different caps through level 50 and then again through level 60 and different formulas apply.  Keyeluke's information is correct for the final level 60 caps, but don't hope to hit those until you're AT level 60.  For details, see the skill guide at www.monkly-business.com.<br><br>Dual Wield: Formula is Level*7 + 5.<br><br>Defense:  From my personal experience, the defense skill is the slowest regular combat skill to raise.  I'm still level-capped in this skill, but it's sometimes a close thing each level.  If you're involved in a lot of battles where you don't draw aggro (grouping with higher levels, etc.) or if you've been killing a lot of high greens for experience (lower chance of skill increase), I could easily believe your defense is under the level cap.<br><br>Mend:  Damn good question.  I've never seen any reliable information on post-100 mend.  I once speculated that if you were under level-cap, the mend amount would be somewhat less (depending on how much below level-cap) than 25%, but this appears to be wrong.<br><br>&nbsp;<br>Osano<br>Level 44 Human Monk<br>Tholuxe-Paells</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
