	   <tr><td colspan=2>Waaaaay to heavy to be used after you start adding some armor better than cured (or at least it was before the new Wu's Fighting Armor came out).  Even if you're super-light, it will seriously increase your need to bank.  Plus, I view the 2HB as primarily a training tool for the uber 2HBs later in the game.  In that case, the speed of the bamboo bo (20 vs. 24) is important as you will train up faster and be able to toss your 2HB back in the bank more quickly.<br><br>I prefer to buy ONE item that is viable for a long time -- the Bamboo Bo qualifies for this, while the Bo stick has a very short lifespan of usefulness, and is difficult to resell due to the weight.<br><br>On the other hand, if you're scraping for cash, it's a good suggestion.  It will certainly get the job done in your teens to low twenties, when you're likely to be very light in any event.<br>&nbsp;<br>Osano<br>Level 44 Human Monk<br>Tholuxe-Paells</td></tr>
