	   <tr><td colspan=2>Why start all over again?  Keep your monk, and just work on your 1HB - it'll take you far less time to build that up than to level 14 times all over again.  You can train up your 1HB when you're in a strong group, or by putting a 1HB in your off hand.  It'll go up slowly, and once it's a bit better you can switch to primary.  Or, burn some skill points.  Or, find a group of 6 fighting blues, and ask to train 1HB with them.  You get no xp, but you'll be safe and you don't have to worry about not pulling your weight.  Get the fastest 1HB you can afford - it should make a difference.<br><br>Keyeluke<br>Monk of the Silent Fist<br>Strange Brew<br>Druzzil Ro<br><br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
