<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=9902511408084></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f9902511408084><tr><td id=headerrow><span id=sj><a href=/strategy/classes.html?class=3&mid=9902511408084>RE: Advice</a></span></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?id=39551><span id=Guru>Osano</span></a>, <span id=Guru>Guru</span><br><span id=notbold>171 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Sat, May 19th 1:45 AM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[4.15]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Looks to me like you're doing pretty well at level 20.  Where you have nothing at all, at least get some cured silk pieces (2PP/AC).  Then, with the leftover cash, get yourself a pair of Gem Inlaid Gauntlets for your hands (should be around 100PP).  Now, your AC will be considerably higher and you'll have magic gloves that will serve you well for a long time (I still wear the GI Gaunts myself).<br><br>From there, you can selectively add pieces.  I think your next goal should be a pair of Orc Fang Earrings (100PP/pair) and Golden Fire Wedding Rings (200PP/pair).  Again, these will serve you well at least until level 35, as you continue swapping the rest of your armor out for better lightweight pieces.<br><br>As for where to hunt -- well, loot is just not that great until level 25.  You can try Gargoyle Island starting at level 23 (solo) or in a group now.  Gargoyle Eyes are about 9PP each when sold to merchants.  Of course, getting to Garg Island might be tough for an Iksar.  However, your best bet, in my opinion, is to concentrate mostly on leveling until 25 (LoIO is great for this), then head off to SolA.  SolA is a great dungeon for monks, both experience and loot-wise.  You can camp and pull to the Rug Room at 25 without a problem and if you have a hybrid (who can root and do some light healing) for a partner you can do very well.  You could easily spend levels 25-40 in SolA, leveling reasonably quickly while making good cash.  The dungeon also has some awesome mid-level monk drops.  Again, as an Iksar you're going to have some faction problems on Antonica, but that's something you'll probably be wanting to deal with at some point anyway.<br><br>Good Luck.<br><br>(Edit:  Key and I posted at the same time ... as you can see our advice is similar, although I personally think Wu's are junk)<br>&nbsp;<br>Osano<br>Level 44 Human Monk<br>Tholuxe-Paells</td></tr>
