	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[4.11]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Whoops, this should have been a reply to the root post, not to Keyeluke, who was dead on target.<br><br>I just want to point out that the damage/sec ratios do not take one VERY important thing into consideration.  Your primary weapon damage bonus. e.g. If you factor in a 3 damage bonus for your primary hand per hit, suddenly the baton looks a lot better than before.<br><br>This is why Celestial Fists are so incredible for dishing out damage (and aggro).  Primary hand the speed is generally more important, especially when the ratios are this close.<br><br>Off hand, go for the best ratio.  In your example, Baton Primary and CoT off hand is the "ideal" setup.  This all assumes you are high enough level to enjoy a solid primary weapon damage bonus =)<br><br>Gorthin Spiritcaller<br>51 Shaman BB<br>Drindal<br>43 Monk BB (semi-retired) <br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
