	   <tr><td colspan=2>LJ Vest is AC 12, not 17 ... the stat buff is STA, if I recall.  It will serve you well for a long time, although once you start adding other magical pieces of armor the weight hurts.<br><br>Most monks prefer the Foreman's Tunic to the LJ Vest.  The Foreman's Tunic is AC 10, STR+3, weight 0.0, but will run you 100-150PP.  the Trade-off on AC for the better buff (STR over STA) and weight is considered well worth it.  From there it tends to be the Crystal Covered Shroud, etc. etc.<br><br>Don't worry about that for quite a while though.  You'll probably still be wearing your LJ vest into your mid-20s.<br>&nbsp;<br>Osano<br>Level 44 Human Monk<br>Tholuxe-Paells</td></tr>
