<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=9899198398195></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f9899198398195><tr><td id=headerrow><span id=sj><a href=/strategy/classes.html?class=3&mid=9899198398195>RE: which weapons?</a></span></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?id=35651><span id=Guru>Keyeluke</span></a>, <span id=Guru>Guru</span><br><span id=notbold>192 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Tue, May 15th 5:43 AM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Follow this link:<br><br><a href="http://tinaddar.kung-foo.org/monk1hb.html" target=_new>http://tinaddar.kung-foo.org/monk1hb.html</a><br><br>It will show you that at your level, and for that matter all the way up to 60, a KD is a better weapon than a Wu's stick - in either primary or secondary.  That is strictly on a damage per second basis.  If you scroll down a few posts, you'll see that I had the same concerns recently.<br><br>Two factors to consider beyond the damage per second figures, though - the Wu's stick is much faster and is far more likely to interrupt casters, and the damage you get from the proc at level 35 will alter the equation. I'd suggest you stick with your current setup for now, and put the KD in your off-hand either when you start fighting caster mobs that do serious damage, or when you get to 35 - you'll want the proc to happen more often.<br><br>In the meantime, if you have the cash (which I'm guessing you might) keep your eyes open for a jade mace to replace your Wu's stick.  At 9/18, it's a better weapon than both the Wu's and the KD, and it is as fast as the Wu's.<br><br>Keyeluke<br>Monk of the Silent Fist<br>Strange Brew<br>Druzzil Ro<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
