	   <tr><td colspan=2>Hail, all my lvl 11 Monk , Salap, just earned his first fighting baton , thru the boring collection process for HQ bear skins. he earned enough plat to buy a fighting Baton. Now here is the question,<br>He has been using a 2hb Bamboo Bo up until now. To gain 1hb skill, should i get another cheap, rusty whatever club in my off hand & use the Baton in my main , or should i put the Baton in my off hand & train both H2H & 1hb. i think my 1hb skill is at 19 & my h2h is around there too, due to my excesive use of the Bamboo bo. I also have full cured silk for armour with orc fang earrings & jagged bands on my fingers, My higher level Pally started Salap reasonably well to catch up to other freinds that have lvl 12 characters on my server. Salap is wearing gem inlaid gauntlets too , to kill magic only critters. My intent is to keep all his skills maxed. But i would like to max the 1hb quickly , so he can join the Buds & be able to deal out some damage.<br>The other question , I have , is that when Salap gets a new magical attack, like tiger claw, recently, should i maintain the round kick, or just train the newest skill. i need some advise here. I would hate to find out in 20 levels later that i should have maintained a round kick as well as the newer attacks??<br>Salap<br>level 11 Monk<br>Lanys T'Vyl<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
