<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=98988094695222></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f98988094695222><tr><td id=headerrow><span id=sj><a href=/strategy/classes.html?class=3&mid=98988094695222>RE: 1HB skill gain??</a></span></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?id=35651><span id=Guru>Keyeluke</span></a>, <span id=Guru>Guru</span><br><span id=notbold>192 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Mon, May 14th 6:55 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>I'd offer the suggestion to leave your off hand open.  You can train your H2H that way - albeit more slowly than your 1HB.  You're very well equipped for a lvl 11, and you'll be able to safely handle the mobs that will get your skill up - you'll kill them more slowly, but your equipment should keep you safer than the average lvl 11 monk.  At 11, your fist is a 6/36.  I'd guess that any piece of crap weapon you use will have a lousy delay, and, it being in your off hand, will do little to speed up your 1HB practice appreciably.  So, work the H2H in there, and once you get 1HB maxed, put the baton in your off hand and practice up H2H the rest of the way.  I don't think you'll want to let H2H stay where it is for a couple more levels, if that's how long it takes to practice your 1HB up - though with the baton's 20 delay, it might go up rather quickly.<br><br>At higher levels, you'll need Kick, Eagle Strike, Dragon Punch, and Flying Kick.  Kick apparently works with Instill Doubt - it's not really that important, because all it seems to govern is the small amount of melee damage that's done on a successful ID.  Still, may as well practice it up.  Eagle Strike and Dragon Punch are used in lvl 50+ disciplines, so if you plan to get that high, keep them up.  Flying kick is your premier special attack at high levels.  At lvl 39, I can kick for 90+ points of damage.  Round Kick and Tiger Claw, to the best of my knowledge, can be left to languish.  That is, of course, unless you're a deeply anal retentive sort - like a friend of mine - and want all your skills maxed.<br><br>It's good you have your 2HB up - I've noticed that 2HB is where monks typically lag behind.  It's also good that you're getting to your H2H and 1HB now, before you get too high level and find yourself stuck with horrid skills in these categories.  Keep up with all 3, and you'll be ahead of the game.<br><br>Keyeluke<br>Monk of the Silent Fist<br>Strange Brew<br>Druzzil Ro<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
