<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=98988132995213></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f98988132995213><tr><td id=headerrow><span id=sj><a href=/strategy/classes.html?class=3&mid=98988132995213>RE: Damage Question</a></span></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?id=35651><span id=Guru>Keyeluke</span></a>, <span id=Guru>Guru</span><br><span id=notbold>192 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Mon, May 14th 7:02 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>I've never heard of a 'damage cap' on fists.  As far as I know, fist damage goes up 1 point every level to 50, and delay decreases 1 point every level to 50.  I've been told that maximum damage is governed by the equation Damage * (Str + Skill) / 100, though I've noticed that I sometimes hit for a little more, so there may be an additional factor involved.  There is also a damage bonus beginning at level 25, but I think that's irrelevant to your question.  Based on that, I'd say your H2H damage is about right, and you'll see it go up at 20 both because of the increased damage factor and because your skill will increase.  Hope this helps somewhat.<br><br>Keyeluke<br>Monk of the Silent Fist<br>Strange Brew<br>Druzzil Ro<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
