	   <tr><td colspan=2>My personal advice, and you may find many who will disagree, is to spend the money on a Tinkerer's pack, at somewhere under 6K.  Weight 1.0 10 slot 100% weight reduction.  I'm saving my coins for one, and it's taking a long time.  Your 2 fighting batons will suit you well for some time yet - I still use one in my primary at level 39.  The pack will let you collect cashworthy loot without hitting your AC, and you'll be able to fight effectively and collect cash, which you can then use to buy the other things you like.  Reasonably priced upgrades from a fighting baton are a Wu's stick at 7/18 or a Cane of Tranquil at 11/25.<br><br>If you decide to go for the pack, get a friend with high charisma to help you - from what I hear, it'll save you a few hundred plat.<br><br>Keyeluke<br>Monk of the Silent Fist<br>Strange Brew<br>Druzzil Ro<br><br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
